WEBVTT

00:07.132 --> 00:09.926
♪ ♪

00:10.552 --> 00:12.220
(door opens)

00:12.220 --> 00:15.432
(birds chirping outside)

00:15.432 --> 00:17.726
- Hey.
- Oh hi, Sam! Come on in!

00:17.726 --> 00:20.562
- I'm in the right place, right?
- Yep, this is it. (laughs)

00:20.562 --> 00:22.814
- Can I put my bag here?
- Sure. Just on the chair.

00:22.814 --> 00:24.733
- That's good.
- Okay.

00:24.733 --> 00:27.402
I have, um...

00:27.402 --> 00:29.362
my sheet music and a tape.

00:29.362 --> 00:31.656
Beautiful. Why don't you
set it here for a second?

00:31.656 --> 00:34.409
- We're gonna...
- Okay.

00:34.409 --> 00:36.578
We're gonna sing something.

00:36.578 --> 00:40.415
I'd like you to sing.
Just a song you love.

00:40.415 --> 00:42.667
- Right off top? (nervous laugh)
- Right off the top.

00:42.667 --> 00:44.753
Okay, like, um...

00:45.837 --> 00:48.798
Something you love.
Can be anything.

00:48.798 --> 00:51.801
- Uh--
- Maybe a song you sang
when you were a kid.

00:51.801 --> 00:53.803
L-like "Here Comes
Peter Cottontail" or...

00:53.803 --> 00:55.722
- (groans)
- (both laugh)

00:55.722 --> 00:59.100
- Well, something you
sang with your family?
- Hm...

01:00.977 --> 01:03.521
- Maybe a love song.
- (groans, sighs)

01:04.898 --> 01:06.483
Um...

01:08.109 --> 01:09.444
Okay...

01:10.445 --> 01:11.780
Um...

01:13.198 --> 01:15.700
- Well, I like this one.
- Okay.

01:15.700 --> 01:18.995
- Just right here?
- Right here. (laughs)

01:20.997 --> 01:27.003
♪ I can only give you love
that lasts forever ♪

01:27.003 --> 01:31.674
♪ And a promise to be
near each time you call ♪

01:31.674 --> 01:34.385
♪ And the only heart I own ♪

01:34.385 --> 01:37.305
♪ For you and you alone ♪

01:37.305 --> 01:40.642
♪ That's all
that's all ♪

01:40.642 --> 01:44.145
- So, you get the idea. (laughs)
- No, no, no. Keep going.

01:44.145 --> 01:45.355
(sighs)

01:47.565 --> 01:49.484
(exhales)

01:49.484 --> 01:53.530
♪ I can only give you
country walks ♪

01:53.530 --> 01:56.616
♪ In springtime ♪

01:56.616 --> 02:02.163
♪ And a hand to hold
when leaves begin to fall ♪

02:02.163 --> 02:05.875
♪ And a love
whose burning light ♪

02:05.875 --> 02:10.046
♪ Will warm the winter night ♪

02:10.046 --> 02:12.298
♪ That's all ♪

02:13.091 --> 02:15.718
♪ That's all ♪

02:15.718 --> 02:19.222
♪ And there are those,
I am sure ♪

02:19.222 --> 02:21.808
♪ Who have told you ♪

02:21.808 --> 02:24.811
♪ They would
give you the world ♪

02:24.811 --> 02:27.814
♪ For a toy ♪

02:27.814 --> 02:31.067
♪ All I have are these arms ♪

02:31.067 --> 02:33.820
♪ To enfold you ♪

02:33.820 --> 02:39.784
♪ And the love
time can never destroy ♪

02:41.828 --> 02:43.454
That's it. (soft laugh)

02:49.168 --> 02:50.879
That was lovely.

02:50.879 --> 02:52.297
Thanks.

02:53.256 --> 02:55.341
(exhales)

02:56.634 --> 02:58.595
And you've given me chills,

02:58.595 --> 03:01.764
just like you did
the first time
I heard you sing.

03:01.764 --> 03:05.101
Oh, Sam, do you
remember singing

03:05.101 --> 03:06.853
"Have Yourself a Very
Little Christmas"

03:06.853 --> 03:09.480
- with your
high school choir?
- Yeah.

03:09.480 --> 03:11.774
I remember thinking how rich

03:11.774 --> 03:14.152
and mature your sound was.

03:14.861 --> 03:16.446
(sighs)

03:16.446 --> 03:19.324
Really, very special

03:19.324 --> 03:21.367
for someone that age.

03:21.367 --> 03:22.493
(sniffles)

03:22.493 --> 03:24.162
Oh, Sam.

03:26.414 --> 03:28.583
What song did you bring in?

03:28.583 --> 03:31.794
Oh, the smash hit
"Ave Maria" By Schubert.

03:31.794 --> 03:33.254
(both laugh)

03:33.254 --> 03:36.090
Well, it's one of my favorites,

03:36.090 --> 03:38.968
and I much prefer
the Schubert
over the Gounod,

03:38.968 --> 03:40.345
so there we go.

03:40.345 --> 03:42.639
Well, I'm supposed to sing it
for my friend's wedding but...

03:42.639 --> 03:44.515
- Oh.
- ...you know, I just...

03:44.515 --> 03:47.727
I can't really sing
that style of music, so.

03:47.727 --> 03:50.647
- Classical?
- Yeah. It's just
my voice is so heavy,

03:50.647 --> 03:53.900
and every time I try
to sing it, I just can't...

03:53.900 --> 03:55.944
It's just sorta too light
and flighty or something.

03:55.944 --> 03:58.655
I don't know, I-I--
So...

03:58.655 --> 04:01.449
We have our work
cut out for us. (laughs)

04:02.533 --> 04:04.619
We'll get there.

04:04.619 --> 04:08.122
First, we start
with the breath.

04:08.122 --> 04:09.832
- Okay.
- Okay?

04:11.292 --> 04:12.669
That's perfect.

04:12.669 --> 04:14.170
Relax your knees
a little bit,

04:14.170 --> 04:16.005
roll your shoulders. Okay.

04:16.005 --> 04:19.217
♪ ♪

04:20.093 --> 04:23.221
(birds chirping)

04:27.684 --> 04:29.769
(door squeaks)

04:30.687 --> 04:32.021
- Hey.
- (shuts door)

04:32.021 --> 04:33.940
Hey! How'd it go?

04:33.940 --> 04:35.358
You know, it was okay.
I mean, all we did

04:35.358 --> 04:37.360
was a little breathing so far,
but not bad.

04:37.360 --> 04:39.278
- Okay.
- Brad: Hiya.

04:39.278 --> 04:40.530
Hi.

04:40.530 --> 04:42.407
Wow, what a nice surprise.

04:42.407 --> 04:44.117
- Yeah.
- (all laugh)

04:44.117 --> 04:45.785
- Knock 'em dead.
- Oh, thanks.

04:45.785 --> 04:47.203
(all laugh)

04:50.915 --> 04:52.834
- Oh, my God...
- That was SLS!

04:52.834 --> 04:54.377
- St. Louis Sushi.
- Yes!

04:54.377 --> 04:57.296
- Or shouldn't it be
Sargent Loose Stools?
- (both laugh)

04:57.296 --> 05:00.883
- Sir Liquid Shits.
- (both laugh)

05:00.883 --> 05:03.052
♪ ♪

05:04.971 --> 05:08.224
(chickens clucking)

05:08.224 --> 05:10.143
What about this?
Does this have to go?

05:10.143 --> 05:11.269
Oh, it's all going.

05:11.269 --> 05:13.271
Joel: Okay.

05:13.271 --> 05:16.107
- I'll handle this.
- Okay.

05:16.107 --> 05:17.692
- You want some help?
- No.

05:17.692 --> 05:19.694
(wood clattering)

05:19.694 --> 05:21.988
- (seat squeaks)
- Oh. (laughs)

05:21.988 --> 05:22.947
Wouldn't it be so cool

05:22.947 --> 05:24.866
