07:01.671 --> 07:04.173
You know what I was
thinking though, too?

07:04.173 --> 07:06.467
Like, do you think that
they want the ceremony

07:06.467 --> 07:07.844
to be kind of Jesusy?

07:07.844 --> 07:09.929
Joel, just ask 'em
what they want.

07:09.929 --> 07:11.097
Okay.

07:12.849 --> 07:14.517
Just part of me is like,
what if they say,

07:14.517 --> 07:16.853
"Yeah, we do want
a religious ceremony,"
'cause then I'm li--

07:16.853 --> 07:19.772
- (TV clicks off)
- (nervous laugh)

07:19.772 --> 07:21.149
Sorry,
am I being annoying?

07:21.149 --> 07:24.360
- (laughs)
- No, I just paused it
so we can talk.

07:24.360 --> 07:26.571
No, no. (clears throat)
I'm done, let's watch TV.

07:26.571 --> 07:27.822
- Okay. You sure?
- Yeah.

07:27.822 --> 07:30.116
Because they're about to...
(whistles suggestively)

07:30.116 --> 07:31.742
- Oh, they are?
- Yep.

07:33.077 --> 07:35.830
- Then, press play.
- (laughs)

07:35.830 --> 07:39.208
- This was so boring until now.
- Now, it's good.

07:40.501 --> 07:42.670
Five stars
for male nudity, finally.

07:43.254 --> 07:44.338
Roll over.

07:47.133 --> 07:50.136
- We have a winner.
- Oh, my God, I thought it
was just gonna be a butt.

07:50.136 --> 07:53.890
(giggling)
This is why
we pay the premium.

07:56.809 --> 07:59.812
Is that what
straight people
sex is like?

07:59.812 --> 08:01.939
If you're lucky.

08:01.939 --> 08:05.443
(continues eating popcorn)

08:05.443 --> 08:06.611
(moaning on TV)

08:11.699 --> 08:12.867
Right?

08:12.867 --> 08:15.244
- (playing piano scale)
- (lip trilling and humming)

08:15.244 --> 08:17.246
I don't know, I feel
like I'm forcing it.

08:17.246 --> 08:19.874
Here. Roll your head
to the left.

08:19.874 --> 08:22.835
To the right.
Like a lazy river.

08:22.835 --> 08:24.003
Roll...

08:24.545 --> 08:26.130
Roll...

08:26.923 --> 08:28.090
Now,

08:28.090 --> 08:31.010
breathe low from
the diaphragm, and...

08:31.010 --> 08:34.430
- (plays piano key)
- (trills lips, sighs)

08:34.430 --> 08:37.016
You know, I-I can (trills)
and I can (hums)

08:37.016 --> 08:39.936
but I just can't do 'em
at the same time.

08:39.936 --> 08:42.438
Maybe we can try something else,
like the song or something.

08:42.438 --> 08:43.731
You can do this.

08:43.731 --> 08:47.401
- Let's take it lower
and slower, okay?
- (sighs) Okay.

08:47.401 --> 08:48.903
(plays piano key)

08:49.820 --> 08:51.113
(trills, hums)

08:51.113 --> 08:53.616
- Get your breath.
- I can't sustain it.

08:53.616 --> 08:56.244
- (clears throat)
- No, you can do this.

08:56.244 --> 08:57.662
- Again.
- (inhales)

08:57.662 --> 08:59.830
- Nice deep breath.
- (trills, hums)

08:59.830 --> 09:01.290
- (plays piano note)
- Engine lips.

09:01.290 --> 09:04.627
- (trilling)
- Like a car
right after a tune-up.

09:04.627 --> 09:07.129
- Nice and smooth.
- (laughs)

09:07.129 --> 09:09.548
(trills, hums)

09:09.548 --> 09:12.385
That's good. Okay,
now let's go up the scale.

09:12.385 --> 09:13.803
(plays higher note)

09:13.803 --> 09:17.640
- (playing full scale)
- (trilling, humming along)

09:17.640 --> 09:19.058
That's it, Sam.
There it is.

09:19.058 --> 09:20.393
That wasn't so bad, right?

09:20.393 --> 09:23.646
- (laughs)
- No, it was much
better than not so bad.

09:23.646 --> 09:25.189
Well, we still have
our work cut out for us,

09:25.189 --> 09:26.440
but I think I'm getting it.

09:26.440 --> 09:28.609
- (both laugh)
- Why do you keep saying that?

09:28.609 --> 09:30.653
Well, because you said
that to me in high school.

09:33.281 --> 09:34.907
You said that
I had a heavy voice,

09:34.907 --> 09:37.118
and we had our work
cut out for us.

09:42.456 --> 09:43.958
Sam.

09:43.958 --> 09:48.337
You have a rich,
full instrument,

09:48.337 --> 09:50.548
not a heavy voice.

09:51.591 --> 09:53.175
And everyone has to work hard,

09:53.175 --> 09:55.469
no matter what their gift is.

10:00.266 --> 10:01.892
You're here now.

10:04.937 --> 10:06.731
Let's start fresh.

10:08.441 --> 10:10.151
Okay.

10:10.151 --> 10:12.111
Fresh start.

10:12.111 --> 10:13.571
(both laugh)

10:13.571 --> 10:15.489
There's something to it.

10:15.489 --> 10:18.826
- (wind chimes tinkle)
- (birds chirping)

10:20.786 --> 10:22.913
Sorry.
Didn't mean to interrupt.

10:22.913 --> 10:25.875
- Oh.
- Uh, you look deep in thought.

10:25.875 --> 10:28.210
(laughs) No, not really.

10:28.210 --> 10:29.670
Mind if I sit?

10:29.670 --> 10:31.172
Oh yeah, of course.

10:34.425 --> 10:35.926
(sighs)

10:38.095 --> 10:39.180
(sighs)

10:43.017 --> 10:46.145
(birds chirping)

10:51.108 --> 10:54.236
(Joel typing)

11:01.786 --> 11:04.872
