- Tricia: Yes!

12:25.786 --> 12:27.621
- So, yeah,
should we come in?
- Tricia: Yes.

12:27.621 --> 12:29.790
Oh, of course.
Yes, please come in.
(giggles)

12:29.790 --> 12:31.375
Oh, it smells great in here.
Oh, shoes off?

12:31.375 --> 12:32.626
Oh, no, you're fine,
you're fine.

12:32.626 --> 12:34.378
So, now we're
getting into more of the,

12:34.378 --> 12:35.796
um, outdoor looks.

12:35.796 --> 12:38.549
This is depending on, you know,
where you land venue-wise,

12:38.549 --> 12:39.675
- of course.
- Mm-hmm.

12:39.675 --> 12:41.343
- This is--
- (glass clinking)

12:41.343 --> 12:43.471
Oh, are you okay, Sam?

12:43.471 --> 12:44.930
- Oh yeah.
- Tricia: Okay.

12:44.930 --> 12:47.183
- Just that, those are--
Those are breakable.
- Okay. Sorry.

12:47.183 --> 12:49.185
And this is one of
my personal favorites.

12:49.185 --> 12:51.353
Um, I call it
denim and diamonds.

12:51.353 --> 12:53.898
Susan:
It's pretty!
I like this plate.

12:53.898 --> 12:55.649
Tricia:
Girl. Same.

12:55.649 --> 12:57.485
It is gorgeous,
isn't it, honey?

12:57.485 --> 12:59.028
It's like--
It's like a...

12:59.028 --> 13:00.779
